                       "message":  "MENUBAR-RECONCILE-DRAINTEST: status-doc reconcile for #287/#288 + render_frame drain test\n\nPost-menu-arc deep-audit cleanup (human chose \"doc reconcile + render_frame\ntest\"). Docs + 1 test + 1 rustdoc; 0 production logic; 0 Cargo.toml.\n\nDOC RECONCILE (forward-only, the #285 pattern - prepend, never rewrite): records\nthat the File menu bar landed FUNCTIONAL (#287 substrate + #288 wiring), so\nOpen/Save/Save-As are now menu-discoverable AND functional, not keyboard-only.\nSupersedes the now-false \"menu-entry wiring still open / keyboard-only\" note (the\nlone Layer-1 status-doc lie the audit found), narrowing the surviving still-open\nto the MenuRegistry::resolve data-driven dispatch (W08 registry) + Edit/View/Play\nmenus + accelerators + plugin entries.\n- Status.md / HANDOFF.md: prepend a 2026-06-02 snapshot above the SAVEAS one.\n- plans/BASELINE.md: prepend a \"### 2026-06-02 - File menu bar landed FUNCTIONAL\"\n  subsection above the 2026-06-01 Save-As subsection.\n- change.md: a 2026-06-02 entry above the pinned REPO TRANSFER line.\n\nTEST (editor-shell lifecycle/tests.rs): render_frame_drains_menu_commands_at_its_top\ncloses the audit\u0027s P2 gap - the four route tests called drain_and_route_menu_commands\nDIRECTLY; none drove render_frame, so the load-bearing top-of-render_frame drain\nplacement (before the surface/window borrows) was structurally untested. The new\ntest enqueues Command::Save, calls render_frame() on a headless shell (which\nearly-returns via the guarded render_frame_egui_only, but the top drain runs\nfirst), and asserts the save hook fired + the bus marked saved. A refactor moving\nthe drain below the borrows would fail this test (and reintroduce the E0502 borrow\nhazard the placement avoids).\n\nRUSTDOC (editor-egui-host lib.rs): EguiHost::render header + Flow step 2 still\ncalled menu rendering a \"future dispatch\"; updated to record the top File menu bar.\n\nProvenance: the 2026-06-02 post-menu-arc read-only 5-axis deep audit (authority\nintact; no kernel-cavity pressure; this drained the lone Layer-1 status-doc lie +\nthe P2 test gap). MenuRegistry::resolve wire-vs-ratify is the named next frontier\n(deferred).\n\nGate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
